  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "L2 English Teacher",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>We are seeking a compassionate and dedicated Preschool Teacher (L2 Certified) to support children from vulnerable families by delivering a safe, nurturing, and structured learning environment that fosters holistic development and inclusion.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Design and deliver age-appropriate learning experiences that promote children’s cognitive, social, emotional, and physical development</li><li>Establish and maintain a warm, secure, and inclusive classroom environment that encourages active learning and belonging</li><li>Observe, document, and assess children’s learning progress and developmental needs to tailor support effectively</li><li>Build trusting and respectful relationships with children and their families to enhance engagement and support</li><li>Collaborate with colleagues to ensure consistent care and coordinated support for children’s well-being</li><li>Manage children’s safety, well-being, and daily routines to maintain a structured and secure setting</li><li>Implement and uphold centre policies and programmes that address the needs of families requiring additional support</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>L2 Certification recognised by ECDA</li><li>Diploma in Early Childhood Care & Education or equivalent</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Demonstrate patience, care, and passion for working with young children</li><li>Apply sensitivity and cultural awareness when working with children from diverse and vulnerable backgrounds</li><li>Communicate effectively and collaborate within a team environment</li></ul>",
